The aim of this philanthropic gesture was to assist the poor and financially-challenged students to attain their dreams in securing admission into tertiary institutions and acquiring knowledge that will give them better opportunities to have a good life in the future. A statement signed by the media aid to Dr. Gwamna, Ibrahim Sani Shawai, quoted her as saying that the gesture was to provide the opportunity for everyone to get good, quality and resounding education irrespective of their background. She added that providing this opportunity for the young ones in the society would help give them hope towards self-development. She urged the candidates to put in more efforts in their studies, adding that education would help them unlock their potentials in life. Family Trust and Care Foundation is a non-profit, non-partisan organisation committed to assisting the poor and vulnerables in the society.